"dist</filename> im Homeverzeichnis von OTRS. Kopieren Sie diese Datei nach "
"<filename>.fetchmailrc</filename> und erweitern Sie die Datei um die Daten "
"Ihrer E-Mail-Accounts (siehe Beispiel 7-1)."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><example><title>
#: en/content/administration/email/email.xml:166
msgid ".fetchmailrc"
msgstr ".fetchmailrc"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><example><para><programlisting>
#: en/content/administration/email/email.xml:170
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"#poll (mailserver) protocol POP3 user (user) password (password) is (localuser)\n"
"poll mail.example.com protocol POP3 user joe password mama is otrs\n"
msgstr ""
"#poll (mailserver) protocol POP3 user (user) password (password) is (localuser)\n"
"poll mail.example.com protocol POP3 user joe password mama is otrs\n"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/email.xml:178
msgid ""
"Don't forget to set the .fetchmailrc to 710 (\"chmod 710 .fetchmailrc\")!"
msgstr ""
"Vergessen Sie nicht, die Zugriffsrechte von <filename>.fetchmailrc</"
"filename> auf 710 zu setzen."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/email.xml:182
msgid ""
"With the <filename>.fetchmailrc</filename> from the Example 7-1 above, all "
"email will be forwarded to the local OTRS account, if the command "
"<command>fetchmail -a</command> is executed. Set up a cronjob with this "
"command if you want to fetch the mails regularly."
msgstr ""
"Wird das Kommando <command>\"fetchmail -a</command> mit dieser Konfiguration "
"ausgeführt, werden alle E-Mails auf das lokale OTRS-Konto weitergeleitet. "
"Richten Sie ggf. einen Cronjob ein, wenn die E-Mails regelmäßig geholt "
"werden sollen."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><title>
#: en/content/administration/email/email.xml:188
msgid ""
"Filtering/dispatching by OTRS/PostMaster modules (for more complex "
"dispatching)"
msgstr ""
"Filterung/Verteilung über PostMaster-Module (für komplexere "
"Verteilungsszenarien)"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/email.xml:191
msgid ""
"If you use the bin/otrs.PostMaster.pl or bin/otrs.PostMasterMailbox.pl "
"method, you can insert or modify X-OTRS header entries with the PostMaster "
"filter modules. With the X-OTRS headers, the ticket system can execute some "
"actions on incoming mails, sort them into a specific queue, change the "
"priority or change the customer ID, for example. More information about the "
"X-OTRS headers are available in the section about <link linkend=\"adminarea-"
"postmasterpop3-account\">adding mail accounts</link> from the OTRS Admin "
"page."
msgstr ""
"Falls die <filename>bin/otrs.PostMaster.pl</filename> oder <filename>bin/"
"otrs.PostMasterMailbox.pl</filename> Methoden verwendet werden, können X-"
"OTRS-Header mit Hilfe der PostMaster-Filtermodule in die eingehenden Mails "
"eingefügt bzw. bereits vorhandene X-OTRS-Header verändert werden. Mit Hilfe "
"von X-OTRS-Headern kann das Ticket System bestimmte Aktionen für Mails "
"ausführen, z. B. diese in eine bestimmte Queue einsortieren, sie einem "
"bestimmten Kunden zuordnen, die Priorität ändern usw. Eine nähere "
"Beschreibung der X-OTRS-Header finden Sie im Kapitel zum <link linkend="
"\"adminarea-postmasterpop3-account\">Einrichten von Mail-Accounts</link> "
"über den Administrations-Bereich von OTRS."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/email.xml:196
msgid "There are some default filter modules:"
msgstr "Es gibt verschiedene Standard-Filtermodule:"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><note><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/email.xml:201
msgid ""
"The job name (e.g. $Self-&gt;{'PostMaster::PreFilterModule'}-&gt;"
"{'JobName'}) needs to be unique!"
msgstr ""
"Der Jobname (z. B. $Self-&gt;{\"PostMaster::PreFilterModule\"}-&gt;{\"Jobname"
"\"}) muss eindeutig sein!"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/email.xml:206
msgid ""
"Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::Match is a default module to match on "
"some email header (e.g. From, To, Subject, ...). It can set new email "
"headers (e.g. X-OTRS-Ignore: yes or X-OTRS-Queue: spam) if a filter rule "
"matches. The jobs of the Example 7-2 can be inserted in <filename>Kernel/"
"Config.pm</filename>"
msgstr ""
"Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::Match ist ein Standard-Modul, um  einige "
"E-Mail-Header (z. B. From, To, Subject) zu prüfen und dann den neuen E-Mail-"
"Header zu setzen (z. B. X-OTRS-Ignore: yes oder X-OTRS-Queue: spam)."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><example><title>
#: en/content/administration/email/email.xml:210
msgid ""
"Example jobs for the filter module Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::Match"
msgstr ""
"Beispiel-Jobs für das Filtermodul Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::Match"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><example><para><programlisting>
#: en/content/administration/email/email.xml:214
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    # Job Name: 1-Match\n"
"    # (block/ignore all spam email with From: noreply@)\n"
"    $Self-&gt;{'PostMaster::PreFilterModule'}-&gt;{'1-Match'} = {\n"
"        Module =&gt; 'Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::Match',\n"
"        Match =&gt; {\n"
"            From =&gt; 'noreply@',\n"
"        },\n"
"        Set =&gt; {\n"
"            'X-OTRS-Ignore' =&gt; 'yes',\n"
"        },\n"
"    };\n"
"    # Job Name: 2-Match\n"
"    # (sort emails with From: sales@example.com and Subject: **ORDER**\n"
"    # into queue 'Order')\n"
"    $Self-&gt;{'PostMaster::PreFilterModule'}-&gt;{'2-Match'} = {\n"
"        Module =&gt; 'Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::Match',\n"
"        Match =&gt; {\n"
"            To =&gt; 'sales@example.com',\n"
"            Subject =&gt; '**ORDER**',\n"
"        },\n"
"        Set =&gt; {\n"
"            'X-OTRS-Queue' =&gt; 'Order',\n"
"        },\n"
"    };\n"
msgstr ""
"    # Job Name: 1-Match\n"
"    # (block/ignore all spam email with From: noreply@)\n"
"    $Self-&gt;{'PostMaster::PreFilterModule'}-&gt;{'1-Match'} = {\n"
"        Module =&gt; 'Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::Match',\n"
"        Match =&gt; {\n"
"            From =&gt; 'noreply@',\n"
"        },\n"
"        Set =&gt; {\n"
"            'X-OTRS-Ignore' =&gt; 'yes',\n"
"        },\n"
"    };\n"
"    # Job Name: 2-Match\n"
"    # (sort emails with From: sales@example.com and Subject: **ORDER**\n"
"    # into queue 'Order')\n"
"    $Self-&gt;{'PostMaster::PreFilterModule'}-&gt;{'2-Match'} = {\n"
"        Module =&gt; 'Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::Match',\n"
"        Match =&gt; {\n"
"            To =&gt; 'sales@example.com',\n"
"            Subject =&gt; '**ORDER**',\n"
"        },\n"
"        Set =&gt; {\n"
"            'X-OTRS-Queue' =&gt; 'Order',\n"
"        },\n"
"    };\n"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><para>
#: en/content/administration/email/email.xml:244
msgid ""
"Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::CMD is a default module to pipe the "
"email into an external command. The output is given to STDOUT and if the "
"result is true, then set new email header (e.g. X-OTRS-Ignore: yes or X-OTRS-"
"Queue: spam). The Example 7-3 can be used in <filename>Kernel/Config.pm</"
"filename>"
msgstr ""
"Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::CMD ist ein Standard-Modul, um die E-"
"Mails an ein externes Kommando zu leiten. Dessen Ergebniss wird an STOUT "
"ausgegeben und, falls das Ergebnis aus STDOUT true ist, wird ein neuer E-"
"Mail-Header gesetzt (z. B. X-OTRS-Ignore: yes oder X-OTRS-Queue: spam)."

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><example><title>
#: en/content/administration/email/email.xml:248
msgid ""
"Example job for the filter module Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::CMD"
msgstr ""
"Beispiel-Job für das Filtermodul Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::CMD"

#. type: Content of: <section><section><section><example><para><programlisting>
#: en/content/administration/email/email.xml:252
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    # Job Name: 5-SpamAssassin\n"
"    # (SpamAssassin example setup, ignore spam emails)\n"
"    $Self-&gt;{'PostMaster::PreFilterModule'}-&gt;{'5-SpamAssassin'} = {\n"
"        Module =&gt; 'Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::CMD',\n"
"        CMD =&gt; '/usr/bin/spamassassin | grep -i \"X-Spam-Status: yes\"',\n"
"        Set =&gt; {\n"
"            'X-OTRS-Ignore' =&gt; 'yes',\n"
"        },\n"
"    };\n"
msgstr ""
"    # Job Name: 5-SpamAssassin\n"
"    # (SpamAssassin example setup, ignore spam emails)\n"
"    $Self-&gt;{'PostMaster::PreFilterModule'}-&gt;{'5-SpamAssassin'} = {\n"
"        Module =&gt; 'Kernel::System::PostMaster::Filter::CMD',\n"
"        CMD =&gt; '/usr/bin/spamassassin | grep -i \"X-Spam-Status: yes\"',\n"
"        Set =&gt; {\n"
"            'X-OTRS-Ignore' =&gt; 'yes',\n"
"        },\n"
"    };\n"

